  "props": [
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        0.0,
        0.0,
        2.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 3.141592653589793,
      "message": "THE PULSE ROOM\n\nA chamber of beating drums — one for every walker, every keeper, every shaped daemon currently alive in the realm. A drum stops if its keeper falls.\n\nThe drumkeeper listens. He has been listening for a long time."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        -2.5,
        0.0,
        -1.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "DRUM: WYRDKING BONELORD\n\nA deep slow drum, low and hollow. Beats once every long breath. The hide is bone-white."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        -2.5,
        0.0,
        0.0
      ],
      "rotation_y": 1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "DRUM: WYRD TOMATO\n\nA quick light drum, the rhythm slightly off-kilter, as if it can't decide which beat is the strong one. Painted leaf-green."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        -2.5,
        0.0,
        1.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "DRUM: THE CODEX KNIGHT\n\nA steady drum with three beats, then a pause. Hide painted with the marks of an older Sigilkeep. The keeper has not yet been faced."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        2.5,
        0.0,
        -1.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": -1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "DRUM: THE MIRELAKE THING\n\nA wet, slow drum. The drumhead is leather treated with something dark. Beats on a long count."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        2.5,
        0.0,
        0.0
      ],
      "rotation_y": -1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "DRUM: THE BURNT SHEPHERD\n\nA cracked, bright drum. The fire-marks on it are old. Beats fast, then long pauses."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        2.5,
        0.0,
        1.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": -1.5707963267948966,
      "message": "DRUM: KHORGAUL\n\nThe largest drum in the room. The beat is so slow you can stand and listen and not hear it twice.\n\nIt is still beating."
    },
    {
      "type": "npc",
      "pos": [
        0.0,
        0.0,
        0.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 3.141592653589793,
      "name": "Drumkeeper Hesh",
      "body_color": [
        0.55,
        0.45,
        0.4,
        1.0
      ],
      "hat_color": [
        0.78,
        0.65,
        0.45,
        1.0
      ],
      "idle_hint": "[E] Speak with the drumkeeper",
      "dialog_tree": {
        "start": "root",
        "nodes": {
          "root": {
            "speaker": "Drumkeeper Hesh",
            "text": "*he is sitting cross-legged in the centre, eyes closed, listening. The drums beat around him in a slow round.*\n\nQuiet, walker. The room is counting.\n\n...all of them are still going. The realm endures.",
            "choices": [
              {"label": "What happens when one stops?", "next": "stop"},
              {"label": "Whose drum is the largest?", "next": "large"},
              {"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}
            ]
          },
          "stop": {
            "speaker": "Drumkeeper Hesh",
            "text": "Then the keeper has fallen. The realm hears the silence. The drum is taken down and the wall is left bare for a season, then a new drum is hung — for whoever rises in their place.\n\nA bare wall is not a sad thing here. It is a kept promise.",
            "choices": [{"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}]
          },
          "large": {
            "speaker": "Drumkeeper Hesh",
            "text": "*his voice goes very quiet.*\n\nKhorgaul's. The slow one. Some days I forget it is there, because the beats are so far apart. Some days I remember and have to sit down for a while.\n\nHe is still going, walker. That is information. Take it as you will.",
            "choices": [{"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}]
          },
          "bye": {
            "speaker": "Drumkeeper Hesh",
            "text": "Walk well. The drums will tell me when you've done something."
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ],
